body_html:
After some searching, is this the tutorial that you're following?

https://github.com/JieHe96/iOS_Tensorflow_ObjectDetection_Example

It looks like this tutorial adds its own Makefile for building the tutorial:

https://github.com/JieHe96/iOS_Tensorflow_ObjectDetection_Example/blob/452dbcb5a4fdd20de0d2b4df4a25bdd8f34c2bda/config/makefile/Makefile_ios

That Makefile_ios isn't compatible with the master branch of TensorFlow... I'd suggest filing an issue against that tutorial. However, it might be compatible with the r1.4 branch of TensorFlow, so you could try checking out that branch then rerunning the script.

body:
After some searching, is this the tutorial that you're following?

https://github.com/JieHe96/iOS_Tensorflow_ObjectDetection_Example

It looks like this tutorial adds its own `Makefile` for building the tutorial:

https://github.com/JieHe96/iOS_Tensorflow_ObjectDetection_Example/blob/452dbcb5a4fdd20de0d2b4df4a25bdd8f34c2bda/config/makefile/Makefile_ios

That `Makefile_ios` isn't compatible with the `master` branch of TensorFlow... I'd suggest filing an issue against that tutorial. However, it might be compatible with the `r1.4` branch of TensorFlow, so you could try checking out that branch then rerunning the script.
